      "https://img.castlecore.uk/smailholm-tower-5.jpg"
    ],
    "desc": "Smailholm Tower is a peel tower at Smailholm, around five miles (8 km) west of Kelso in the Scottish Borders. Its dramatic situation, atop a crag of Lady Hill, commands wide views over the surrounding countryside. The tower is located at grid reference NT637346, just west of Sandyknowe farm, and is now a Scheduled Ancient Monument in the care of Historic Environment Scotland. In June 2007, it was awarded the maximum \"five-star\" status as a tourist attraction from VisitScotland, a rating bestowed on only eight other sites in Scotland.",
