    "image": "https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-traquair-house.jpg",
    "imgSource": "CDN",
    "gallery": [],
    "desc": "Traquair House, approximately 7 miles southeast of Peebles, is claimed to be the oldest continually inhabited house in Scotland. Whilst not strictly a castle, it is built in the style of a fortified mansion. It pre-dates the Scottish Baronial style of architecture, and may have been one of the influences on this style. The estate contains the famous Traquair Brewery.",
