      "https://img.castlecore.uk/mingary-castle-main-4.jpg",
      "https://img.castlecore.uk/mingary-castle-main-5.jpg"
    ],
    "desc": "Mingary Castle, also known as Mingarry Castle, is a castle situated one mile southeast of the small village of Kilchoan in Lochaber, Scotland. Nestled on ridge of rock overlooking the sea, it was considered a strategically important site in terms of communication with overseas areas and as an entranceway to the Sound of Mull. Mingary is roughly hexagonal in shape with nine-foot-thick walls, thicker on the seaward side. The remains of the castle are protected as a category A listed building.",
    "type": "castle",
    "period": "13th century",
    "rating": 4,
