    "mapsLink": "https://www.google.com/maps/search/Raemoir%20House%20Aberdeenshire%20scotland",
    "image": "https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-raemoir-house.jpg",
    "imgSource": "CDN",
    "gallery": [],
    "desc": "Raemoir House is a Category B listed Georgian mansion house located in Banchory, Aberdeenshire, Scotland. Its origins date back to the Ha'Hoose which was built in 1715 during the Georgian Era. Raemoir changed hands a number of times and remained a private residence until 1943, when it became a hotel. Over the centuries Raemoir has been renovated a number of times. The prominent architect John Smith even contributed to Raemoir's present appearance. Today Raemoir House is run by Neil and Julie Rae, who acquired the property in 2010 and ran it as a hotel and events venue for some years. Since 2017, Raemoir House has been an exclusive use venue for weddings, events and house parties.",
    "type": "castle",
    "period": "18th century",
    "rating": 3.8,
